{A young Spassky outplays the legendary attacking artist Nezhmetdinov on his own
turf. Queens come off early (7.Qxd8+), and Spassky simply grinds the resulting
endgame, finishing with a clean king-walk: a reminder that the Alekhine is a winning
weapon, not just a provocation.}
